Rostelecom Surges in Moscow Trading, Paring 3-Week Tumble

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-12T15:28:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/rostelecom-gains-most-in-2-months-as-alfa-says-drop-overdone-.html
OAO Rostelecom,  Russia ’s dominant
fixed-line telephone operator, jumped the most in almost two
months after Alfa Bank said the stock’s drop is “overdone.”  The shares surged 15 percent to 146.91 rubles by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow, their biggest increase since June 17. The
stock has tumbled 31 percent in the last three weeks.  “The stock is trading at a significant discount to its
emerging market peers,” analysts Peter Szopo and Iouli Matevossov, wrote in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  